       things from those conversations?"

Claude: "Absolutely — you can create a custom extraction skill that
         teaches Multiplist to find exactly what matters in coaching
         conversations. Let me help you define it.

         When you look back at coaching sessions, what do you wish
         was already pulled out and organized?"

User: "I want to find breakthrough moments, when clients resist
       change, and what homework they committed to."

Claude: "Those are great categories. Here's what I'd create:

         Name: Coaching Session Extractor
         Categories:
         1. Client Breakthroughs — Moments of insight, perspective
            shifts, or emotional clarity
         2. Resistance Patterns — Recurring objections, avoidance,
            or limiting beliefs
         3. Homework Commitments — Specific actions committed to
            before next session

         Each one gets extracted with full provenance — you'll see
         exactly where in the conversation it appeared.

         Does this look right?"

User: "Yes, perfect!"

Claude: [calls create_skill with the definition]

Claude: "Done — your Coaching Session Extractor is live. Want to
         test it on an existing conversation, or save a new one
         and extract with it?"

User: "Let's test it on my last coaching call."

